{
  "stem": "26111.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And even though there were at least one, maybe two servants in the house-- a maid, a cook, et cetera-- in the apartment, I don't know whether they were live-in or not.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I'm sure that the nanny was probably live-in.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] That-- the, the division of labor between the parents in the '20s, 1920s, was-- in, in, in that kind of society was simply-- had, as a result, that the father was far less in touch with the-- with the children and that they were really the preserve of the mother and the-- and the staff.",
      "word_count": 59
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, we would see him every day, for meals at the very least.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't know at what, what age, exactly, we started sitting at the adult's table.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I do recall that when we were much smaller, we had a small table set for us at the side of the big table.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we would eat somewhat earlier, but there was always an overlap before my parents took their places at the big table.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that-- that's somewhat vague.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The timing is somewhat vague.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And maybe I invented part of this because usually the children eat before adults do, so I can't swear to that.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But anyway, the small table is definitely-- was definitely there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And this was particularly clear-- and is particularly in my memory because when people were invited, which was very often the case, we-- both of us-- both my sister and I-- dearly resented being relegated to the children's table.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Oh, children's table, we can't sit-- we are not really fully fledged beings.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We were relegated to the small table.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Even though everybody was very nice to us, but we looked up-- literally up-- at the big table and were envious--",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--as are all children.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Same room.",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
